29/10/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The United States on Tuesday (October 28th) welcomed Serbia's decision to return its ambassador to Washington.
Serbia initially recalled its ambassadors from all countries that recognised Kosovo's unilaterally declared independence in February.
The US Embassy in Belgrade issued a statement saying it views Serbia's decision as an important step in the development of bilateral relations and expressed hope these relations will continue to grow.
(AP, Makfax - 28/10/08)
